com.ibm.watson.dsm.util

Class AbstractKeyedListenerManager<KEY,LISTENER,DYN_DATA,STATIC_DATA,NOTIFY_DATA>

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.ibm.watson.dsm.util.AbstractKeyedListenerManager<KEY,LISTENER,DYN_DATA,STATIC_DATA,NOTIFY_DATA>
  • Direct Known Subclasses:
    AbstractClientServer

    public abstract class AbstractKeyedListenerManager<KEY,LISTENER,DYN_DATA,STATIC_DATA,NOTIFY_DATA>
extends java.lang.Object
    Maintains a list of keyed listeners. Listeners can be added and removed and called. Subclass simply implements #callListener(Object, Object) to call the interface-defined LISTENER method, and makes a call to #notifyListeners(Object, Object) when the listeners are to be called.
    Author:
    dawood
